Petroleo Brasileiro SA Chief
Executive Officer Jose Sergio Gabrielli and Minister for Mines
and Energy Edison Lobao attend an event concerning pre-salt  oil
fields  in Sao Paulo. Gabrielli will speak about the state-run
oil companyâ€™s investments and Brazilian industry.  GOVERNMENT:
*President  Dilma Rousseff  attends the opening of an event on
policies for developing a new middle class at 9 a.m. She meets
with visiting Canadian President  Stephen Harper  at 11:20 a.m.
and then the two sign agreements and speak to the press at 12:30
p.m. Rousseff also meets with head of the civil aviation agency
Wagner Bittencourt at 4:30 p.m.
*Finance Minister  Guido Mantega  has internal meetings.
*Central bank president Alexandre Tombini has meetings in
Brasilia.  WHAT TO WATCH:
*Petrobras CEO Jose Sergio Gabrielli, Minister for Mines and
Energy Edison Lobao speak at an event at Hotel Caesar Business
in  Sao Paulo  at 9 a.m.  ECONOMY:
*FGV Inflation IGP-DI at 8 a.m.
*FGV CPI IPC-S at 8 a.m.
*Central bank weekly economists survey at 8:30 a.m.
*Trade balance (FOB) - weekly at 11:00 a.m.
*CNI Capacity Utilization at 2 p.m.  EQUITIES:
*Brasil Foods (BRFS3 BZ) hired Banco BTG Pactual to sell some of
its assets, Chief Executive Officer Jose Antonio Fay said.
*Souza Cruz (CRUZ3 BZ) named Andrea Martini CEO from January.
*B2W (BTOW3 BZ) forecast double-digit sales growth in the second
half.  MARKETS
*The Bovespa index rose 0.3 percent to 52,949.22.
*The real gained 0.8 percent to 1.5761 per dollar.  To contact the reporter on this story:
